<paragraph id="EB598C50D8BCC790D38AA89F28408B7D" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Length (including tegmen): ♂, 5.2mm.</paragraph>
<caption id="9324ABA0035A82DAD06C8A492DD7BB6E" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph id="9B8AF0213D397BA670F42B182E16F8EA" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figures 53-60. 
<taxonomicName id="DC4AAB7595B5EB24831D065403FF1984" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pedionis (Pedionis) tabulatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tabulatus" subGenus="Pedionis">Pedionis (Pedionis) tabulatus</taxonomicName>
Li, Dai &amp; Li sp. n. 53 Male pygofer side, lateral view 54 Subgenital plate, lateral view 55 Aedeagus, ventral view 56 Aedeagus, lateral view 57 Style, dorsal view 58 Dorsal connective 59 Connective, dorsal view 60 Connective, lateral view.
</paragraph>
